  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Best Desk Lamp for Eye Care 2026</h1>
      <div class="meta">Updated June 2026 · Evaluated 9+ models</div>

      <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
        <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</a></li>
          <li><a href="#ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</a></li>
          <li><a href="#quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-overall">Best Overall</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-budget">Best Budget</a></li>
          <li><a href="#buying-guide">Buying Guide</a></li>
          <li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <p>If you stare at a screen for eight or more hours a day, the right desk lamp is not optional — it is the single cheapest upgrade that reduces eye strain and afternoon headaches. The wrong lamp creates glare on your monitor, throws uneven light that forces your pupils to constantly adjust, and eats desk space you need for a keyboard and mouse. We evaluated nine LED lamps based on their specifications and design features to find which ones actually protect your eyes without wasting your surface.</p>

      <h2 id="how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</h2>
      <p>We evaluated 9 LED desk lamp models based on product documentation, specifications, feature analysis, and pricing comparison. Our evaluation methodology follows the <a href="/how-we-test/">ToolStep review protocol</a>, analyzing product documentation, specifications, features, and pricing. Each product was assessed across identical criteria to ensure fair comparison.</p>
      <p>We evaluated each product on four criteria: Performance (30%), Build Quality (25%), Value (20%), and Ease of Use (25%). Scores were compiled from specification analysis and feature evaluation, not marketing claims. Lux output was assessed based on manufacturer-stated brightness specifications across all levels. Color temperature accuracy was assessed based on manufacturer-published Kelvin values, and screen glare was evaluated based on lamp design, light distribution features, and mounting flexibility. We also evaluated desk footprint based on base or clamp dimensions.</p>

      <h2 id="ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</h2>
      <p>Our rankings are based on weighted scoring across four dimensions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Performance (30%)</strong> — Lux output, color accuracy, and glare control</li>
        <li><strong>Build Quality (25%)</strong> — Arm rigidity, joint durability, and LED longevity</li>
        <li><strong>Value (20%)</strong> — Price-to-performance ratio compared to alternatives</li>
        <li><strong>Ease of Use (25%)</strong> — Adjustability, desk footprint, and control layout</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</h2>
